Package: OncoPath
Type: Package
Title: OncoPath Functions for Clinicopathological Research
Version: 1.0.1
Date: 2026-07-16
Authors@R: person(given = "Serdar", family = "Balci", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), email = "serdarbalci@serdarbalci.com", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7852-3851"))
Maintainer: Serdar Balci <serdarbalci@serdarbalci.com>
Description: Provides specialized oncology and pathology visualization
 tools for clinicopathological research, adapted from the
 ClinicoPath jamovi module. Helps researchers create
 comprehensive patient follow-up plots including waterfall plots
 for treatment response analysis and swimmer plots for patient
 timeline visualization. Features RECIST (Response Evaluation
 Criteria in Solid Tumors) criteria analysis, ggswim integration,
 comprehensive clinical event tracking, diagnostic test
 meta-analysis with bivariate modeling and Holling proportional-hazards
 summary ROC methods, and IHC
 (immunohistochemistry) heterogeneity analysis for pathology
 biomarker studies. For comments, suggestions, feature requests
 or reporting bugs, please open an issue at
 <https://github.com/sbalci/OncoPath/issues/>.
